Michigan State University on Friday became the second public university in the state to announce it would not raise tuition for the 2020-21 amid the COVID-19 outbreak.
Buy Photo Dr. Samuel Stanley, president of MSU, speaks during his first board of trustees meeting Friday in East Lansing.
For undergraduates from outside of Michigan, tuition and fees cost $39,830.
MSU tuition is operating under a two-year budget approved in June 2018.
The budget established a tuition freeze for all undergraduate students, so rates did not increase for the 2019-20 academic year.